items.name: Sexy Cop Uniform
items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

To support me you can buy me a coffe at https://ko-fi.com/antonioriolo

Training settings:

33 images, 25 steps, 9 epochs, you find many epochs (with test images using plot xy script) on my Patreon while supporting me.


Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9

  • LORA weight for txt2img: reccomended 0.5-0.8

  • Keys: wearing sexy cop uniform

I'm not very happy about this model. It doesn't work as i expected.

First advice i give you it's to put a big weight on the keyword, like "(wearing sexy cop uniform:1.5)" and use always the model with atleast a 0.5-0.6 weight or you will see a bikini girl with a cop cap hat.

You can prompt something like "blue uniform" or "black uniform" to have different types of cop uniform (other then different colors)

One other thing that have worked is to start the prompt with "a woman next to a police car". As you can see from some example images.

I also tryied to had handcuffs and cop glasses as keywords but they do not seem to work, atleast i didn't manage to let them work. Handcuffs keyword produce nonsense, cop glasses produce normal glasses, even if there are many training images with cop glasses.

My mistake might be that i had to do more steps to train something like this, but i'm not sure that it could give a better result.

Anyway, problems aside, if you follow the weight instructions, you will end up with some good sexy cop images, Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.description:
General Info

This LoRA is very experimental and exists due to my desire to create a capable, gundam-focused model. Due to not having the necessary equipment to create a whole gundam checkpoint i tried this on a LoRA. Another reason i attempted this is, that the Aurora model from Luna (https://civitai.com/models/40199/aurora) is pretty capable in general so it encouraged me to try training on that one. The LoRA is simply a test so it should be reviewed with that in mind. Though i am happy for everyone who tries it out, tries to improve it or can offer what i can not to the community.

Usage

The model has been trained using Kohya so you probably want to use it in the same way as you use other Kohya models. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. Feel free to play around with settings etc. to eventually draw any use out of this

items.name: NAPHAEL-D
items.description:
NAPHAEL-D aspires to create exquisite art with minimal prompting.

  1. You have the option to utilize Stability AI's Original VAE, or experiment with other VAE models.

  2. This exemplary set of prompting and generated data (from the 3rd thread posted image)

    Prompt: 2girl, portrait, realistic, bare shoulders, naked towel, sidelighting, wallpaper, nsfw,

    Negative prompt: (worst quality:2, low quality:2), (zombie, sketch, interlocked fingers, comic),

    Generation Data :

    Eta: 0.68, ENSD: 31337, Size: 512x1024, Seed: 2158295917, Model: naphael-D, Steps: 25, Sampler: Euler a, CFG scale: 7, Clip skip: 2, Model hash: ea4980559b, Hires steps: 10, Hires upscale: 2, Hires upscaler: 4x-UltraSharp, Denoising strength: 0.3

    For a more 2.5D feel, consider including a "realistic" prompt

  3. For optimal results, try a clip skip of 1 or 2, and enable quantization in K samplers, with an ENSD of 31337 and Eta at 0.68.

  4. If the character in the prompt is far away, Hires.fix may be necessary, with options such as R-ESRGAN 4x+Anime6b or 4x Ultrasharp, with 10 steps at 0.1 up to 0.3 denoising.

  5. Experiment with various prompts and parameters to generate different artwork.

I encourage you to explore this model and experiment with different prompts and parameters. Constructive feedback is welcome, and please share your stunning artwork here for all to enjoy. Thank you for your support, and let's have some fun!

I'm relatively new to this field and hope to contribute what I can to this community.

items.name: Star vs. the forces of evil - Star Butterfly
items.description:
If you like the LoRa, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) for the sake of motivation and stuff ;D

For usage guidance, look into the About this version box for more information and click on Show more to get all trigger words and combinations (The trigger words in the Details box are a pain to manage).

Please contact me here on civitAi or on Twitter if you want to provide the LoRa in a generation service.

About

Well, this week I realized that there are more than 2 sessions of this series. (I watched it years ago, and it was nice back then ^^).

So I went back and watched the first two sessions, and occasionally made screen caps of the characters, because I was thinking: I want to make LoRa available to all the characters that I care about.

I start the first batch with Star Butterfly the magic crazy girl, in most of her outfits (she changes them quite often, which is nice, considering that this is a western animation series). And the existing LoRa didn't tag the outfits properly, which is the main reason why I created my own ^^.

Additionally there will be Marco's Mom and Jacky Lynn coming up this weekend, they are currently in training :D

Training

This was fun and due to the fact I wanted to train most of her outfits (there maybe some missing) I ended with 155 images. (v1 had just 128 but I actually forgot to put two more outfit to the training data. So I created v1.1)

Additionally instead of using repeats I moved to use epochs instead... this way I have way more control over the end result ^^ (But I think I nailed it with 32 epochs ;D)

This is the first time I've specifically tagged the model for specific outfits, it worked quite well in most cases (first I used deepbooru for tagging, but there was just too much unnecessary junk, so I started from scratch, and although the dataset tag editor helped a lot, it was still a pain).

Maybe I'll make an updated version to get a bit more training data for the outfits that didn't go so well. I only used the animated series, but maybe fanart / the comics could solve the problem of those missing outfits ^^

  • For all outfits you can add or remove her horn hairband and her wand but it likes to multiply a lot xD

  • green squid outfit Her iconic green outfit with the pink squid on it for completion add purple striped pantyhose

The outfits that didn't go to well:

  • princess dress Was only trained with 6 images from the opening and first scene

  • bloodmoon outfit The outfit she wore on the bloodmoon ball, didn't really stick :<

items.name: Yurika Misumaru - Martian Successor Nadesico
items.description:
Our favorite captain from the Nadesico. She is the last of my planned Nadesico characters as Inez Fressange and Erina Kinjo Won are already complete. Interestingly Yurika is like a yandere but with zero violent tendencies. Instead of killing your harem she would help you recruit and manage it :P The lora is trained mostly on Watanabe Yoshimasa's and Hell And Heaven's work. So support those artists if you can. Specially Watanabe Yoshimasa who has made dozens of great Nadesico doujins.

The Lora is rather forgiving and works fine with: <lora:YurikaMisumaru:0.75>, YurikaMisumaru, CaptainUniform,

It seems stable from .3 to 1.2, at 1.3 it is very interesting and somewhat artistic(not good for general use but nice in it's own way).

As for her outfits, images of her out of uniform are scarce so i didn't bother to add triggers for them only 2 are properly added:

  • CaptainUniform

  • CaptainHat

You may want to set her hair color and eye color as it varies and a good part of the dataset is in monochrome. Honestly I am confused if her eyes are green or blue and her hair changes from blue to purple whenever, so YMMV just pick what you like.

You might be able to possible make the lora spit her idol costume, wedding_dress and naked_apron with some coaxing as they are inside the dataset.

All in all a very nice and mild tempered LORA, I seem to have a harder time when using screencaps of 90s anime than with modern stuff or artwork. Might be all the noise and graininess they have even after filtering them. The ones I have made mostly from screencaps have been a bit of a nightmare(Erina Kinjo Won and Ifurita... I also blame their lipstick).

I'll add the tag summary with the dataset so you can experiment.

Some interesting tags from the dataset:

  • white_gloves

  • military_uniform

  • thighhighs

  • pantyhose

  • garter_belt

  • garter_straps

  • capelet

  • stockings

  • pencil_skirt

  • school_uniform

  • wedding_dress

items.description:
Ahoy me crews!

Shiver me timbers! How are ye all doing? I hope that everyone is doing well and fine this week. After long days of testing and preparing the LORA. I am happy to announce that Trieste Lora can now be used by all of you fellow shikikans. \(￣︶￣*\))


Thank you so much for all of your love and support. I have made some beautiful art with this Lora and this Lora can both be used on realistic or anime models on stable diffusion.


This Lora is equipped with 3 official costumes and 1 fanart costume that you can use. I've made this Lora with 20 Epochs and 14 epochs. You can test out which ones that you like the most. I prefer to use the 20 epochs for more strict official outfits and the 14 epochs for scenes that do not use the official costumes. YOU CAN GET THE 14 EPOCHS ON MY PIXIV FOR FREE
